Text.Value: Was I that obvious?
These people are still in danger.
I like you, Wyll. And I want to know you better.
If only faith was enough to ward off every bully of the wilds.
I just wanted to check up on you, that's all.
I'm not sure that I am. But it means something that you think so.
But who am I fooling? I can't go back to that life.
I wish you were there, but I'll respect your need for peace.
I love the way your nose wrinkles up when you get the scent of a lead for the first time.
You must be Volo in disguise, out here to harangue me for some tales of the Frontiers.
Though I can't say I've earned the honour.
You're impossible.
Maybe another time. Now, you've got a party to get back to. Don't forget, tonight is about you.
Saving the people of the grove was all the satisfaction I could ask.
I know how to have fun! I have lots of fun every day!
I just wanted a quick chat. I'll leave you to it.
You don't unsettle me, you know that.
We all die. But life's still worth the living. Otherwise, what's the point of it?
I feel spikes begnning to sprout in places they really shouldn't.
Oh! Seems I stumbled ahead of myself. Wouldn't be the first time.
We have won this day! Danger is for tomorrow.
Clearly Mol has put you up to stealing my britches so you can turn them into a flag for her gang.
Maybe just a little.
There will be another time for us.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: (SCENE) Wyll places his hand on Tav's shoulder. Short player

Text.Value: You're good at it. You've given me some just by being here.
They aren't ready to get on the road on their own.
I'm afraid my feet are firmly planted to the ground this evening.
You were hoping for some peace and quiet out in the forest, and I have ruined your night entirely.
I don't need a party on top of that!
Have a laugh, make some noise. I'll by my charming self before you know it.
A kiss? Well - I can't say I'm not tempted. But not here, not now.
You're right, but we need to give them hope.
I once beat the Baldurian record for the most sarabandes danced in a single evening.
Sorry it has you feeling rough tonight.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The player and Wyll stoops to share a quick kiss.

Text.Value: Damn right I'm fond of you.
Keep trying!
You're halfway right.

EditorData.logicalname: IF MOL STEALING BRITCHES OPTION WAS SAID

Text.Value: Ha! In truth, I always enjoyed a bit of pomp.
Agh, Hells! I was hoping you wouldn't notice I was gone.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The player approaches Wyll, who is lost in thought. He is visibly startled to see you appear.

Text.Value: Gods know why. You'd be well within your rights to burn me alive.
Your words cheer me more than any party could.
I better come clean - I wanted a kiss.
You have many talents, but subtlety isn't one of them.
Why else? There couldn't be another reason.
I had years of lessons but in truth, it's all about your partner.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Wyll eyes you up and down.

Text.Value: If not a dance, then maybe a kiss.
For you, it's as clear as cool water you have that heroism within you.
I'm a devil. I love the people from the grove, but I unsettle them deep down.
But not tonight. Tonight is about you.
It's a long shot, but - maybe you've grown fond of me.
Leave.
Ouch! You don't need to mock me when I'm feeling low.
Thanks. It's good to know someone's looking out.
In truth, I don't feel in a festive mood, and didn't want to cast a grey cloud over the night.
You cut quite a fine figure. I can just imagine leading you with an entire ballroom watching.
But off with you. This is your day! Have a dance. Enjoy the music.
Maybe.
It's a long shot, but - maybe you've grown fond of me. Gods know I've grown fond of you.
Still - it's a night to remember. You've made sure of that.
As I seem to unsettle everyone nowadays.

EditorData.NodeContext: Wyll seems truly mournful, just for one moment.

Text.Value: So? If they die, they die. That's life for you.
If so, I'm afraid I must remain a passing fancy. If not, well, it wouldn't be my first misjudgement.
Too many reasons to count. I might share them someday.
Aw, by Balduran's elbow, I can't stay feeling gloomy with you looking at me like that.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: A moment of quiet passes between Wyll and Tav. Tav looks expectantly towards Wyll.

Text.Value: To our kind, those features just make you more attractive.
Sounds like some pretty words for sulking to me!
Have some faith. Whatever happens, they'll survive it.
I - well, then. Erm, you've got a party to get back to. After all, tonight is about you.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Smiling and slightly embarrassed. Short player version.
The player and Wyll share a quick kiss.

Text.Value: The world spits on those partial to devils. I'm hardly a prime catch.
Let me think... Why are you really here?
Don't complain. We're all still alive, aren't we?
Not that I'd necessarily object.
Because I like you. And I want to know you better.
Ahem.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Wyll realises he may have been better off not revealing that.

Text.Value: That's not true. You're an incredible person, Wyll.
I would give anything to have seen it.
*Sigh.* You drive a hard bargain. But just the one.
Karlach got lusty at the party, didn't she?
You don't want a devil at your party.
I imagine you're fairly skilled with your form, too. That would be a sight to behold.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Wyll looks you up and down.

Text.Value: Twelve impossible deeds every day before the sun reaches its apex.
Don't beat yourself up. We are doing the best we can, together.
What's on your mind?
Are you all right?
Of course I noticed. It was no party without you.
These people are still in danger. A thousand perils still threaten them.
I just wanted to see if my friend was all right, nothing more.
You're running away from Gale's cooking.
Oh, I'm deeply proud of you. A touch less so of myself.
Can't you tell why I really followed you out here?
It's delicious, don't get me wrong, but that man wouldn't eat a vegetable unless Mystra herself commanded it.
I can say it even more nicely.
You just have some fetching horns! I'm envious.
The Blade is my best self. On my best days, I've even lived up to the name.
What exactly do you think you're doing sulking out here? Get your arse back to the party!
I shouldn't be celebrated tonight. That's why I left.
I - well, then. Erm, you've got a party to get back to. After all, tonight is about you.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Smiling and slightly embarrassed. Tall player version.

Text.Value: Really? I'm honoured.
Oh shush. Let yourself have fun.
I mean - the Blade hasn't exactly lived up to his own reputation. Here you are, cheering me up when I almost tore you down.
I mean - the Blade hasn't exactly lived up to his own reputation.
Too much honey-wine can do that. You should watch yourself.
Ah, I'll be fine. Seeing you has cheered me more than you can know.
Then we share a similar affliction. For I've grown fond of you too.
Oh! I will safeguard my undergarments with care.
You're safe another day. Really, that should be enough.
She's started a huge fire, and you're trying to save my life.
You have a vow from the Blade. He will show you a wonderful time, another night.
Let's drop this, shall we?
Maybe a kiss would prove my affections.
Karlach, the creature from Hell, will still threaten them. As will a thousand other perils.
Clearly to practice your forest tracking.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Wyll plays dumb in a little game with the player for this section
EditorData.NodeContext: Jokingly, and trying to avoid talking about what he knows is obvious

Text.Value: Why not? You never know what the future holds.
There will be another time for us.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: (SCENE) Wyll places his hand on Tav's shoulder. Tall playert player

Text.Value: Come on, you're exaggerating. Not that much has changed.
I'm, ahem, soberly pondering my state of affairs, and not wishing to drag a single happy soul into a state of melancholy.

EditorData.NodeContext: Making fun of his own sulking

Text.Value: Nope. Guess again.
What a cruel disguise! My nerves started hammering the second I thought she was the one looking for me.
What a cruel disguise! My nerves started hammering the second I thought he was the one looking for me.
What a cruel disguise! My nerves started hammering the second I thought they were the one looking for me.
Some time alone beneath the stars, and I'll be back to my old self. Promise.
You pull them off far more finely than I do.
Now, you've got a party to get back to. Don't forget, tonight is about you.
Much to the exhaustion of the good ladies and gentlemen of the Gate.
If not a dance, then maybe a kiss.
If only half the world had half the heart you do.
You must have stumbled out here by complete accident.
Horns this sharp will pop the balloons, you see. And the guests won't take kindly to scars quite so monstrous.

EditorData.NodeContext: Very jovially, trying to make light of the situation

Text.Value: We've saved the grove, and everyone hails us as heroes.
I haven't even managed to kill one measly devil. I'm hardly a prime catch. Certanily not for the great gith warrior from Crche K'liir.
I haven't even managed to kill one measly devil. I'm hardly a prime catch.
But Karlach is dead, and Gods know how many other of my victims were people like her.
Well, it just so happens I'm fond of you too.
That's the way of the Blade.
You don't need to be the Blade of Frontiers for me, just be yourself.
Actually, I thought I might steal a kiss.
What can I do to cheer you up?
Maybe we could pretend. Just for one night.
Ha! Oh, the Blade doesn't sulk. I was just reflecting on what has happened, and not wanting to be Mister Serious at a celebration.
Maybe a kiss would prove my affections.
I want to dance with you.
I better come clean - I wanted a kiss.
Actually, I thought I might steal a kiss.

Synopsis:
This dialog replaces EA version in Gustav mod!

After the goblin hunt celebration party, this companion has made arrangements to get intimate with the player at night. Note: this can only happen if player already knows about Mizora
